We will be doing a regensis for the zkSync 2.0 testnet on Tuesday 2022Âπ¥4Êúà12Êó• 17:00. Regenesis will cause a full network reset and will re-launch testnet from scratch. Why are we doing a regenesis? We are actively working on network performance upgrades, and some changes are breaking while we're still in the testnet phase. Once we accumulate a number of such changes, we do a scheduled regenesis. How long do we estimate downtime? Up to 2 hours, but we will post an update in the -testnet-status channel and ping users with the @deleted-role role (you can get the role in -roles) What does this mean for users and developers? All activity on testnet will be erased.
